description:
United Raw Pet Foods Inc., a fast-growing, leading manufacturer of quality raw pet foods in Canada and a subsidiary of the Dane Creek Capital Corp., is recruiting for an energetic, driven Intermediate Accountant to assist with full-cycle accounting and financial functions of our Canadian based manufacturing operations. The role includes the preparation of our consolidated financial statements, financial reporting and maintaining controls and processes for all retail locations.




We are looking for a candidate that is a driven and personable team member with a “can-do” attitude. The ability to handle changing priorities with equanimity while maintaining open and effective communication are important attributes that you will need to be an effective member of our team.





We are currently recruiting for the following role:





Accountant (Intermediate)





Job Role Summary





This Accountant role will primarily be involved in preparing and maintain the bookkeeping and multiple general ledgers. This position will be responsible for preparing and posting journal entries, including year-end general entries, reconciling accounts, running payroll, and managing payables. In addition, some preparation of other statistical, financial, and accounting reports may be required. This position reports to the Corporate Controller, Manufacturing.





Essential Functions






Maintain and monitor company accounting records and conduct monthly/quarterly reviews;

Assist with processing accounts payable;

Process customer invoicing and maintain accounts receivable control and sub ledger;

Prepare financial statements (e.g., balance sheet, P&amp;L, statement of cash flows);

Maintain internal controls processes and systems;

Work with the retail management team on product pricing, costing and margins;

Develop and maintain financial policies and procedures across all retail locations;

Manage the timely completion of all company statutory filings (i.e. PST &amp; HST returns);

Achieve operational efficiencies throughout all locations;

Preparation of financial reports for management to support the company’s reporting requirements to various stakeholders;

Approve and process company expenses;

Perform account reconciliations;

Perform data entry;

Meet ad hoc requests as necessary.








Qualifications





Please note that while the following qualifications are desired, United Raw will consider reasonably equivalent combinations of education and experience when assessing candidates.





Minimum 3 years’ experience in an Accountant role is required

A Bachelor's Degree in the related field is required

Proficient with computer software, particularly

High level and ability to demonstrate professionalism and confidentiality

Strong attention to detail

Demonstrates a positive work ethic and team player attitude

Excellent organizational, time management and prioritization skills

Self-motivated

A love of pets

Brookfield Renewable is looking for an Accountant to complete the team of the Brookfield Global Transition Fund (BGTF). This role will play an integral part in establishing processes, maintaining books and records and fund reporting to our BAM Counterparts. In this role, you will regularly collaborate with members of Brookfield’s Business Services Group Accounting team and support the Manager and Senior Manager on fund related matters. We welcome dedicated, and team-oriented individuals who are passionate about being an integral part of our dynamic organization and helping it thrive. We are looking for people who are interested in both professional and personal growth!








What we Offer



Competitive salary, bonus, benefits from day 1, 3 weeks’ vacation, Defined Contribution Pension Plan

Opportunity for growth and development

Exposure to different businesses, geographies, and teams

A collaborative, open, dynamic, and fast paced environment






Responsibilities



Facilitate the monthly, quarterly and annual financial close process for the BGTF companies;

Integrate new investments into our processes, systems, and reporting packages;

Determine and prepare timely and accurate general journal entries to ensure accurate financial reporting;

Maintain, monitor and reconcile monthly general ledger reconciliations;

Perform bank and other account reconciliations;

Liaise with multiple internal and external stakeholders on topics including chargeback processes, company and project creation, system structure, and time tracking.

Prepare monthly fund reporting documentation by investment.

Support other departments such as Financial Reporting, Financial Planning and Analysis, and Consolidations in achieving successful internal and external reporting through providing variance analysis and supporting their understanding of the Accounting records;

Create and maintain process documentation for BGTF’s accounting processes.

Provide support to auditor questions and requests;

Perform ad hoc projects as needed during the year;







 Requirements



Excellent communication, interpersonal and organizations skills;

Strong drive to be part of an exciting period of growth for the company;

Strong time-management skills and ability to multi-task;

Attention to detail and ability to meet tight deadlines, particularly around month and quarter end close;

Flexibility to work additional hours at quarter end or during peak periods;

Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to use sound judgment;

Ability to manage and prioritize competing responsibilities;

Ability to work as part of a team and strong communication skills in English are required;

Knowledge of French considered an asset;

Thrives in a team-based and dynamic environment.











Qualifications



3+ years’ experience performing full-cycle accounting;

Experience creating process documentation

Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or equivalent in relevant work experience;

Complete or nearing completion of CPA designation;

Demonstrated knowledge of accounting principles (IFRS and fund accounting is an asset);

Solid MS Excel skills (including vlookup and pivot tables) with the ability to learn new systems quickly.






Overview


Brookfield Renewable is one of the core businesses under Brookfield Asset Management (“Brookfield”), one of the world’s leading alternative asset managers. Brookfield operates in over 30 countries and manages over $600 billion of real assets focused on real estate, infrastructure, renewable power, private equity, and credit. Brookfield is publicly listed on the NYSE and TSX.




Brookfield Renewable is one of the world’s largest owners, operators, and developers of renewable power, with $59 billion of power assets under management. Our portfolio of hydropower, wind, utility-scale solar, distributed generation, and storage assets extends across North America, South America, Europe, India, and China, totaling over 21,000 megawatts of capacity, and nearly 6,000 generating facilities globally. Leveraging over 120 years of operating experience and industry-leading innovation, we drive value across our extensive clean energy platform and deliver innovative renewable power solutions that accelerate the world towards a low-carbon future. Our value extends well beyond the clean energy we produce to fuel a sustainable, growing economy. From our extensive renewable power fleet, we make positive economic, social, and environmental impacts in the communities where we live and work.




At Brookfield Renewable, we attract and retain high-performing individuals who are interested in making an impact and being part of a fast-paced and collaborative environment. Join our team to contribute to the success of one of the fastest growing and largest publicly traded, pure play renewable power platforms in the world while supporting decarbonization and greater energy sustainability to facilitate the global transition to a net-zero economy.

