 own a car for displacements at customers.

Company Description


Mikros Animation is a global CGI animation studio located in Paris, Montreal, Los Angeles, Bangalore and London, dedicated to feature films and episodic content. Since its inception, Mikros Animation has always put creativity and CG artistry at the heart of its animation and production activities, allowing our artists to work across a great variety of stories with a high level of stylized craft. So far, Mikros Animation has contributed to ten released feature animations and to numerous high-quality animated series, for the world’s best-known animation studios, either as creative studio, line producer or executive producer. Mikros Animation has also produced more than 250 hours of programming, broadcast by notable channels including Cartoon Network, Nickelodeon, TF1, France TV, Gulli, M6, Gloob, and Super RTL. Our animated episodic content airs and streams globally, in over 180 countries.

At Mikros Animation, we believe great animation is about making real connections with real people. By partnering with filmmakers to unite their creative visions, with our industry-leading craftsmanship and artistry, we create characters that connect with audiences on an authentic and emotional level to bring powerful stories to life.


Job Description


We are looking for a dynamic Production Accountant who will look after aspects of film finance. Responsibilities will include but not be limited to:


Support the financial controller in preparing detailed cost estimates for the run of the projects;

Prepare Analysis to the financial controller on the profitability of each show, and provide insight into opportunities and risks;

Perform cost analysis of ongoing shows;

Controlling, recording and reconciling costs to ensure cost control and preparing regular costs and progress reports for management;

Report, forecast and analyze all future revenues and associated costs on ongoing projects.

Month-end duties: prepare and document month-end entries for the FSSC including revenue recognition

Create customer invoices in Scheduall (billing tool)

Prepare weekly cash forecasts

Prepare and document the required monthly (forecast) or quarterly (QBR)

Participate in the preparation of the budget with the local financial controller

Participate in Tax Credits files compilation

Provide ad-hoc administrative support



Qualifications



3 to 5 years experience

Advanced Microsoft Excel skills (VLOOKUP, Pivot Tables, Sumifs etc.) and abilities to create and work in complex financial models;

Communicant, attached to details but also able to synthesize;

Excellent communication and organizational skills;

Strong attention to detail;

Being able to work effectively under pressure in a fast-paced environment, with a strong sense of urgency to achieve results;

Ability to collaborate with various stakeholders such as HR, Production, IT, and Management;

Strong financial analysis/interpretation skills;

VFX industry knowledge is an asset



